'''无教派穆斯林'''<ref>{{cite book|last1=Ngaima|first1=Samuel|title=Factors to the Liberian National Conflict: Views of the Liberian Expatriates|date=2014|page=17}}</ref>是指不属于一个明确[[伊斯兰教派|伊斯兰教派]]的穆斯林。<ref>{{cite news |last=Benakis |first=Theodoros |date=13 January 2014 |title=Islamophoobia in Europe! |url=http://neurope.eu/article/islamophobia-europe/ |newspaper=[[New_Europe_(newspaper)|New Europe]] |location=Brussels |access-date=20 October 2015 |quote=... the non-denominational Muslims – those who are neither Shiites nor Sounites, but who accept Islam as a religion generally. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160131145036/http://neurope.eu/article/islamophobia-europe/ |archive-date=2016-01-31 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>无教派穆斯林可以指向《古兰经》{{link-en|仪姆兰的家属|Al Imran}}第103节来捍卫这一立场，即要求穆斯林保持团结不要分离。<ref>Intra-Societal Tension and National Integration, p 119, A. Jamil Qadri - 1988</ref>在各种调查中，当问及其属于哪个[[教派|教派]]时，这些穆斯林通常会自我认定为“只是一个穆斯林”。<ref name="Pew"/><ref>{{cite book|last1=Burns|first1=Robert|title=Christianity, Islam, and the West|page=55|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=akWUGyN7fwEC&pg=PA55&dq=%22just+a+muslim%22+non+denominational&hl=en&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22just%20a%20muslim%22%20non%20denominational&f=false|quote=40 per cent called themselves "just a Muslim" according to the Council of American-Islamic relations|access-date=2015-12-10|archive-date=2020-11-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201116085911/https://books.google.ca/books?id=akWUGyN7fwEC&pg=PA55&dq=%22just+a+muslim%22+non+denominational&hl=en&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22just%20a%20muslim%22%20non%20denominational&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>在获得明确的解释之前，这些穆斯林会自己对教义（包括经文和[[圣训|圣训]]）进行{{link-en|格亚斯|Qiyas|推理判断}}或考虑大多数伊斯兰学者的意见。在英语中，这种意识形态的穆斯林还有一个'''Just Muslim'''的称呼。<ref>{{cite book |last1=Mustapha |first1=Abdul |title=Sects & Social Disorder |date=2014 |page=5 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=lIKfBwAAQBAJ&pg=PA5 |quote=of Muslims identified themselves as Sunni, 12 per cent as Shi'a, 3 per cent as Ahmadiyya but 44 per cent as 'just Muslim' (Pew Forum, 2010) |access-date=2015-12-10 |archive-date=2020-09-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200919001101/https://books.google.com/books?id=lIKfBwAAQBAJ&pg=PA5 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Muttitt|first1=Greg|title=Fuel on the Fire: Oil and Politics in Occupied Iraq|date=2012|page=79|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JwMo-NINQ8QC&pg=PA79|quote=A January 2004 survey by the Iraq Centre for Research and Strategic Studies, for instance, asked people which description suited them best Sunni Muslim, Shi'a Muslim or just Muslim'.|access-date=2015-12-10|archive-date=2020-11-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201116085937/https://books.google.com/books?id=JwMo-NINQ8QC&pg=PA79|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Boulting|first1=Ned|title=On the Road Bike: The Search For a Nation’s Cycling Soul|page=155|quote=What is your religion, asked a UN official. Muslim. Are you Shi'a or Sunni. Just Muslim}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Tatari|first1=Eren|title=Muslims in British Local Government: Representing Minority Interests in Hackney, Newham and Tower Hamlets|date=2014|page=111|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=x_4QBQAAQBAJ&pg=PA111|quote=Nineteen said that they are Sunni Muslims, six said they are just Muslim without specifying a sect, two said they are Ahmadi, and two said their families are Alevi|access-date=2015-12-10|archive-date=2020-07-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200729064250/https://books.google.com/books?id=x_4QBQAAQBAJ&pg=PA111|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Lopez|first1=Ralph|title=Truth in the Age of Bushism|date=2008|page=65|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vuNfXxnYWPIC&pg=PA65|quote=Many Iraqis take offense at reporters' efforts to identify them as Sunni or Shiite. A 2004 Iraq Centre for Research and Strategic Studies poll found the largest category of Iraqis classified themselves as "just Muslim."|access-date=2015-12-10|archive-